The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | IPL tops agenda
                                                   IPL tops agenda
                      
	Mumbai: The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI)s 80th AGM, scheduled here on September 24, has a 13-point agenda topping which would be the clearing of the IPL-II accounts, which came under the public scanner following dissension within the BCCI.         
	The expenditure for the IPL, shifted to South Africa, includes a bill of Rs 33 crore to be paid to event management firm IMG. This did not go down well with the members of the all-powerful working committee, and secretary N. Srinivasan wrote to IMG terminating the Boards association with the firm but the move was greeted by protest letters from seven franchises and Sharad Pawar.         
	The AGM is to consider and approve the income and expenditure accounts of IPL II, as per the agenda circulated to the members.         
	Narendra Modi, the Gujarat chief minister, is expected to attend the AGM as the president of the Gujarat Cricket Association. (PTI)                                                                                                                       
